# GitHub Configuration
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
GITHUB_ORG=your-organization-name

# ============================================
# Fine-Grained Token Permissions
# ============================================
#
# Create a fine-grained PAT at:
# https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
#
# WARNING:
# If you are going to query repositories or GHAS alerts from an organization,
# the PAT must be created with that organization selected as the Resource owner.
# It is not enough to create the token from the settings of a user who is Owner
# of the organization. If the Resource owner is your personal account instead of
# the org, requests like /orgs/{org}/repos or /orgs/{org}/code-scanning/alerts
# can return [] or 404 even when the user belongs to the org.
#
# Repository permissions (all repos or select repos):
#   - Code scanning alerts: Read
#   - Dependabot alerts: Read
#   - Secret scanning alerts: Read
#   - Metadata: Read (selected automatically)
#
# Organization permissions:
#   - Custom properties: Read (to query repos by properties)
#                        Write (only if creating/updating properties)
#   - Members: Read (to list org repos)
#   - Administration: Read (for org-level alert queries)
